ility is already underway. Cohen describes a range of public policy and infrastructure initiatives that can encourage cleaner production in the private sector and consumption in everyday life. He argues that the politics, advocacy, and communication around environmental protection must change to emphasize successes, reduce scare tactics, and make sure that the lifestyles and careers associated with a more sustainable world sound attractive to a wide range of people. The book depicts an appealing and equitable future that assures quality of life while protecting the planet.Environmentally Sustainable Growth brings together insights from many disciplines, spanning the latest scholarship and practical experience. Useful for students and courses, this book will be informative for practitioners, managers, analysts, activists, and scholars whose work incorporates environmental sustainability.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnvironmental degradationxPrevention. 0aEnvironmental ethics. 0aEnvironmental policyxEconomic aspects. 0aGreen technologyxTechnological innovations. 0aInfrastructure (Economics)xEnvironmental aspects. 0aNaturexEffect of human beings on. 0aSustainable developmentxPolitical aspects. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Environmental Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074967040uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/cohe2086440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231557535423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231557535/original  a978-3-11-074967-0  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles